1
00:00:00,480 --> 00:00:02,378
<i>Previously on Mad Men...</i>

2
00:00:02,624 --> 00:00:05,672
I assumed that we were
forgetting about that.

3
00:00:05,821 --> 00:00:07,488
Well, I haven't.

4
00:00:07,498 --> 00:00:08,964
His name is Manolo Colón.

5
00:00:09,091 --> 00:00:11,488
He's an army trained
registered nurse.

6
00:00:11,621 --> 00:00:14,374
Is he Spanish from Spain?
Because otherwise, Mother will refuse.

7
00:00:14,944 --> 00:00:16,162
You know, we're losing the war.

8
00:00:16,514 --> 00:00:18,210
Wouldn't know it
from looking around here.

9
00:00:18,407 --> 00:00:20,096
Yeah, it's something, right?

10
00:00:20,568 --> 00:00:23,609
I am going to continue on Chevy
evaluating other people's work.

11
00:00:24,109 --> 00:00:25,502
That's all I can do right now.

12
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:29,664
Call me around 1970 when
they're ready to make an ad.

13
00:00:55,629 --> 00:00:58,589
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

14
00:01:22,053 --> 00:01:26,432
Good morning, Mr. Draper.
Mr. Sterling's inside.

15
00:01:27,624 --> 00:01:29,825
- Do you want ice?
- Coffee.

16
00:01:33,964 --> 00:01:36,199
It's one thing to be near the bar,
it's another thing to be under it.

17
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,944
Sunkist sent us a crate.

18
00:01:38,945 --> 00:01:42,013
I've seen blind people juggle, but
somehow it seems to be beyond me.

19
00:01:42,014 --> 00:01:43,105
Why don't you
just close your eyes?

20
00:01:43,106 --> 00:01:44,576
That's what you did
in the meeting.

21
00:01:44,577 --> 00:01:46,143
Whatever I did, it worked.

22
00:01:46,144 --> 00:01:47,809
- We're in it.
- That's good news.

23
00:01:47,810 --> 00:01:49,244
Step one,
I send it to research.

24
00:01:49,245 --> 00:01:52,447
Step two, you'll need to get that
little idea factory working.

25
00:01:52,448 --> 00:01:54,249
There's only one angle.

26
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:57,384
An orange--
that's orange on TV.

27
00:01:57,385 --> 00:02:00,064
I thought they were pretty clear
they're too cheap to get out of print.

28
00:02:00,065 --> 00:02:01,888
So talk 'em out of it,
or into it.

29
00:02:01,889 --> 00:02:04,958
I'd love to, but I think it
demands a media strategy.

30
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:08,229
Forget research.
Put Harry Crane on it.

31
00:02:09,598 --> 00:02:11,332
- Look at you.
- See?

32
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:13,500
Not all surprises are bad.

33
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:24,416
The ants,
they look like peoples.

34
00:02:24,417 --> 00:02:27,453
He should be right out. Is
there anything I can get you?

35
00:02:27,454 --> 00:02:29,181
I think she would
like a cup of tea.

36
00:02:29,182 --> 00:02:30,949
- In a teacup.
<i>- I'd be more excited</i>

37
00:02:30,950 --> 00:02:33,918
if we didn't have to go
in Ted's plane to present.

38
00:02:33,919 --> 00:02:36,800
- Hello, Mother.
- Hello, Peter.

39
00:02:36,801 --> 00:02:39,236
Manolo, may I speak
with you a moment?

40
00:02:39,237 --> 00:02:41,893
Of course, Mr. Campbell.
Your tea is coming.

41
00:02:41,894 --> 00:02:44,328
I'll be fine.
I'm not a child.

42
00:02:46,532 --> 00:02:48,366
Peggy, would you mind?

43
00:02:51,170 --> 00:02:53,671
Mrs. Campbell,
nice to meet you.

44
00:02:53,672 --> 00:02:56,544
There's no reason for you
to be so formal, dear.

45
00:02:56,545 --> 00:02:59,109
Sit with me.

46
00:03:03,847 --> 00:03:05,216
How are you today?

47
00:03:05,217 --> 00:03:07,150
I can't tell you
how much it relieves me

48
00:03:07,151 --> 00:03:09,452
to see you and Peter reunited.

49
00:03:09,453 --> 00:03:12,422
Well, it was really
a by-product of the merger.

50
00:03:12,423 --> 00:03:14,558
I'm glad you both
swallowed your pride.

51
00:03:14,559 --> 00:03:16,768
If nothing else
but for the good

52
00:03:16,769 --> 00:03:19,036
of the child you have together.

53
00:03:21,507 --> 00:03:22,973
Excuse me?

54
00:03:22,974 --> 00:03:26,502
Oh, I've embarrassed you.

55
00:03:26,503 --> 00:03:29,280
Your son and I are not
together that way.

56
00:03:29,281 --> 00:03:31,207
Trudy, dear, don't deny him.

57
00:03:31,208 --> 00:03:34,475
Don't reject his caresses.

58
00:03:34,476 --> 00:03:35,710
Mrs. Campbell--

59
00:03:35,711 --> 00:03:38,379
I hope you two can someday find

60
00:03:38,380 --> 00:03:41,120
what Manolo and I have found.

61
00:03:42,756 --> 00:03:45,591
I waited long enough

62
00:03:45,592 --> 00:03:49,761
to experience the physical
satisfactions of love.

63
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,568
Did she go
to China for that tea?

64
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:00,505
Thank you for driving
her out to Bud's.

65
00:04:00,506 --> 00:04:02,536
I've paid you
for the extra day.

66
00:04:02,537 --> 00:04:04,416
- I know you don't drive.
- Well, I do,

67
00:04:04,417 --> 00:04:07,806
but not to her satisfaction.

68
00:04:07,807 --> 00:04:10,816
Bob Benson was right about you.
You're worth every penny.

69
00:04:10,817 --> 00:04:12,845
Bob is a wonderful salesman.

70
00:04:12,846 --> 00:04:15,648
Still, I want you to have a
little something off the books.

71
00:04:15,649 --> 00:04:17,516
Mr. Campbell,
I refuse.

72
00:04:17,517 --> 00:04:19,785
It's important to me
that you treat my mother well,

73
00:04:19,786 --> 00:04:21,886
but also
that you treat yourself.

74
00:04:21,887 --> 00:04:25,189
- The pleasure is all mine.
- I know that isn't true.

75
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:34,343
Sally, get in here.

76
00:04:34,344 --> 00:04:36,134
<i>Hello.</i>

77
00:04:38,304 --> 00:04:40,704
- What?
- Julie's mother called and told me

78
00:04:40,705 --> 00:04:43,073
- you were the only two girls on the trip.
- So?

79
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:45,952
You're not staying in a Midtown
hotel with all those boys.

80
00:04:45,953 --> 00:04:47,878
Miss O'Shea is gonna be there.

81
00:04:47,879 --> 00:04:49,280
She's 25.

82
00:04:49,281 --> 00:04:51,424
What's the point
of having a mansion

83
00:04:51,425 --> 00:04:53,383
if you're gonna spend
all your time in here?

84
00:04:53,384 --> 00:04:55,685
Fine, I won't do the Model UN.

85
00:04:55,686 --> 00:04:58,336
- It was his idea.
- Fine, you're not going.

86
00:04:58,337 --> 00:05:00,739
- Can't we stay with Daddy?
- You mean with no one.

87
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:03,275
You hate that Daddy
supports my dreams.

88
00:05:03,276 --> 00:05:07,178
He doesn't think I'm
just a pain in the ass.

89
00:05:07,179 --> 00:05:09,547
Your father is a hero.

90
00:05:09,548 --> 00:05:11,533
Like everything
else in this country,

91
00:05:11,648 --> 00:05:14,850
Diplomacy Club's just
another excuse to make out.

92
00:05:14,851 --> 00:05:16,971
I thought she should join
the Student Congress.

93
00:05:16,972 --> 00:05:18,784
The UN's a joke.

94
00:05:23,145 --> 00:05:26,048
- Oh, you're home.
- Who's this?

95
00:05:26,049 --> 00:05:28,716
This is Mitchell,
Sylvia and Arnold's son.

96
00:05:30,719 --> 00:05:33,321
Nice to finally meet you, Mitchell.
I'm Don.

97
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:38,559
Thanks again, Megan.

98
00:05:45,312 --> 00:05:47,935
What did he want?

99
00:05:47,936 --> 00:05:50,370
Um...

100
00:05:50,371 --> 00:05:54,080
I'm sworn to secrecy, but
he's in a lot of trouble.

101
00:05:54,949 --> 00:05:58,651
- What happened?
- He's 1-A.

102
00:05:58,652 --> 00:06:00,580
But he's in school.

103
00:06:00,581 --> 00:06:02,464
He sent back his draft card

104
00:06:02,465 --> 00:06:05,767
in protest.
They reclassified him.

105
00:06:05,768 --> 00:06:07,335
What did he think
was gonna happen?

106
00:06:07,336 --> 00:06:08,455
Stupid kid.

107
00:06:08,456 --> 00:06:10,790
Don, he knows he screwed up.

108
00:06:10,791 --> 00:06:13,125
He wants to run.

109
00:06:13,126 --> 00:06:16,161
You know, to Canada.

110
00:06:16,162 --> 00:06:17,763
I suppose I could
call my brother-in-law,

111
00:06:17,764 --> 00:06:19,808
but I can't do that
to Sylvia and Arnold.

112
00:06:19,809 --> 00:06:23,068
- Can I?
- Just leave it alone.

113
00:06:23,069 --> 00:06:25,471
- He's so scared.
- He should be.

114
00:06:29,675 --> 00:06:32,844
He can't spend the rest
of his life on the run.

115
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:35,394
I know how you feel,

116
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:37,482
but you don't want him
to go to Vietnam.

117
00:06:37,483 --> 00:06:39,617
Megan, it's not our problem.

118
00:06:45,890 --> 00:06:47,691
Could you get me
another whiskey sour?

119
00:06:47,692 --> 00:06:50,660
- Sure.
- Maybe I'll switch to whiskey sours.

120
00:06:50,661 --> 00:06:52,061
How about
a Shirley Temple, then?

121
00:06:52,062 --> 00:06:55,136
I don't think Dramamine
and booze go together.

122
00:06:55,137 --> 00:06:57,472
I don't think Dramamine and cranberry
juice go together, either.

123
00:06:57,473 --> 00:06:58,940
But I thought we'd be back
on your little plane,

124
00:06:58,941 --> 00:07:00,970
not having a romantic dinner.

125
00:07:00,971 --> 00:07:02,848
Don't you want to celebrate?

126
00:07:02,849 --> 00:07:04,072
I want to live, Ted.

127
00:07:04,073 --> 00:07:05,674
What?

128
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:07,777
He doesn't like flying.

129
00:07:07,778 --> 00:07:09,378
Well, you've seen
how simple it is now.

130
00:07:09,379 --> 00:07:10,752
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

131
00:07:10,753 --> 00:07:14,422
My father died
in a plane... crash.

132
00:07:14,423 --> 00:07:17,519
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

133
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,200
Was he a pilot?

134
00:07:19,201 --> 00:07:20,869
Ha! No.

135
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:22,724
Passenger.

136
00:07:22,725 --> 00:07:24,064
Look, you're driving.

137
00:07:24,065 --> 00:07:25,827
Can we please, please
have another round?

138
00:07:25,828 --> 00:07:28,864
You still have to get home
from White Plains.

139
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:29,997
I'll hail a cab.

140
00:07:30,112 --> 00:07:32,700
He's such a New Yorker.

141
00:07:36,771 --> 00:07:39,339
This is the agency
I always wanted.

142
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:41,608
Ambition, brains, and beauty.

143
00:07:41,609 --> 00:07:43,744
Yeah, but what about him?

144
00:07:43,745 --> 00:07:46,212
I'm gonna cut you
off too, my dear.

145
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:53,120
I should call home.

146
00:07:53,121 --> 00:07:55,421
If the check comes, I'm
sending it to Ocean Spray.

147
00:08:00,704 --> 00:08:01,994
Can you imagine what
it does to his wife

148
00:08:01,995 --> 00:08:04,296
every time he takes that plane?

149
00:08:04,297 --> 00:08:06,397
I guess so.

150
00:08:06,398 --> 00:08:09,408
You don't want me
to talk about his wife.

151
00:08:09,409 --> 00:08:10,843
You don't know
what you're talking about.

152
00:08:10,844 --> 00:08:12,704
But I do.

153
00:08:12,705 --> 00:08:15,206
I've seen that look.

154
00:08:17,312 --> 00:08:19,547
I know, but...

155
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,688
nothing can happen.

156
00:08:22,689 --> 00:08:24,882
And he's in love with you, too.

157
00:08:26,688 --> 00:08:28,285
You're the one
who's in love with him.

158
00:08:28,286 --> 00:08:30,788
Well, I could use an account
and he's been generous.

159
00:08:35,296 --> 00:08:38,230
At least one of us
ended up important.

160
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:42,201
Please tell me
you don't pity me.

161
00:08:42,202 --> 00:08:44,604
I don't.

162
00:08:44,605 --> 00:08:47,073
Because you really know me.

163
00:08:50,777 --> 00:08:53,345
I do.

164
00:08:59,318 --> 00:09:03,652
Ahem--
I should tell you...

165
00:09:03,653 --> 00:09:07,489
I had a very strange
conversation with your mother.

166
00:09:07,490 --> 00:09:09,724
There's no other kind.

167
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:13,060
Well, it doesn't matter.

168
00:09:13,061 --> 00:09:15,968
What did she say?

169
00:09:15,969 --> 00:09:19,839
I think she thought
I was your wife

170
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:24,005
and Manuel was her husband.

171
00:09:24,006 --> 00:09:26,272
My father never
treated her that well.

172
00:09:26,273 --> 00:09:29,856
Maybe that's it. She thinks
she's in love with him.

173
00:09:29,857 --> 00:09:32,191
I can see it.
Manolo is very charming.

174
00:09:32,192 --> 00:09:34,593
I don't think you understand.

175
00:09:34,594 --> 00:09:36,996
She thinks she's...

176
00:09:36,997 --> 00:09:40,253
making love with him.

177
00:09:40,254 --> 00:09:42,888
Tell me exactly what she said.

178
00:09:42,889 --> 00:09:46,336
Did your father ever
give her spa treatments

179
00:09:46,337 --> 00:09:49,606
that released
a "fire in her loins"?

180
00:09:49,607 --> 00:09:52,396
Oh!

181
00:09:52,512 --> 00:09:54,465
Oh, I think I'm gonna be sick.

182
00:09:54,466 --> 00:09:57,769
I'm sorry.

183
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:59,203
I shouldn't have told you.

184
00:09:59,204 --> 00:10:01,312
But I can't get the image
out of my head.

185
00:10:01,313 --> 00:10:02,714
Stop it, please.

186
00:10:02,715 --> 00:10:05,150
I don't even want to think
about her brushing her teeth.

187
00:10:05,151 --> 00:10:08,285
<i>I thought I cut you two off.</i>

188
00:10:09,253 --> 00:10:10,847
Ted.

189
00:10:10,848 --> 00:10:14,432
I have never been less
afraid of flying in my life.

190
00:10:15,486 --> 00:10:17,854
What?
What does he mean?

191
00:10:17,855 --> 00:10:20,290
Nothing.

192
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:22,725
Well, I should get the check.

193
00:10:35,195 --> 00:10:37,897
Honey, who's that gonna be?

194
00:10:44,204 --> 00:10:45,772
- Arnold.
- Is it too late?

195
00:10:45,773 --> 00:10:49,508
For what?
Come in.

196
00:10:49,509 --> 00:10:52,144
Look, I would have
called, but Sylvia is...

197
00:10:53,746 --> 00:10:56,882
Listen, about
this afternoon--

198
00:10:56,883 --> 00:10:59,584
Oh, hello, Arnold.

199
00:10:59,585 --> 00:11:02,287
I'm sorry about my kid
dropping in on you.

200
00:11:03,856 --> 00:11:06,324
I didn't know
if I should tell you.

201
00:11:06,325 --> 00:11:07,792
Well, he figured you would

202
00:11:07,793 --> 00:11:09,494
and I don't want you
in the middle of this.

203
00:11:09,495 --> 00:11:11,663
His mother's treating it
like he's dying.

204
00:11:11,664 --> 00:11:13,665
She doesn't want
anyone to know.

205
00:11:16,101 --> 00:11:17,635
Do you want a drink?

206
00:11:17,636 --> 00:11:21,306
Sit up here drinking while they're
down there slamming the doors?

207
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:26,075
Been meaning to knock
on your door anyway.

208
00:11:26,076 --> 00:11:28,211
You know, catch a game
or something.

209
00:11:28,212 --> 00:11:31,648
I get baseball tickets.
Mostly the Mets.

210
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:33,883
Well, then I'm glad you didn't.

211
00:11:37,622 --> 00:11:40,856
You know, I didn't
even know he left school.

212
00:11:40,857 --> 00:11:43,693
Sylvia says
she didn't know either.

213
00:11:44,928 --> 00:11:46,929
She's doing that
a lot lately--

214
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:50,265
lying about little things.

215
00:11:50,266 --> 00:11:52,668
Could tell something's
been wrong all year.

216
00:11:54,805 --> 00:11:58,072
- Another Manhattan?
- Nah. No.

217
00:11:58,073 --> 00:12:01,309
Should have never
let him go to Paris.

218
00:12:01,310 --> 00:12:03,911
He got there right in
the middle of the riots.

219
00:12:03,912 --> 00:12:05,814
His French is excellent.

220
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:09,451
I think he got a lot of girls

221
00:12:09,452 --> 00:12:12,285
as an expatriate revolutionary.

222
00:12:12,286 --> 00:12:14,287
Could kill him right now.

223
00:12:15,557 --> 00:12:16,923
There has to be a way.

224
00:12:16,924 --> 00:12:19,226
Oh, believe me,
everybody's an expert on it.

225
00:12:19,227 --> 00:12:21,662
Sylvia's father was
suddenly Clarence Darrow.

226
00:12:21,663 --> 00:12:25,632
It's thrilling to see a plumber
interpret international law.

227
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:28,167
You're one of the top
surgeons in the country.

228
00:12:29,436 --> 00:12:31,303
You must know somebody.

229
00:12:31,304 --> 00:12:33,205
I know a lot of people,
but it doesn't matter.

230
00:12:33,206 --> 00:12:36,008
It doesn't matter
if he goes back to school.

231
00:12:36,009 --> 00:12:39,044
He's 1-A. His induction
could be tomorrow.

232
00:12:39,045 --> 00:12:41,280
He's on a damn list
for the rest of his life.

233
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:47,519
On some level you have
to admire his idealism.

234
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,987
You sound like Sylvia.

235
00:12:48,988 --> 00:12:51,890
But she doesn't really
buy his bullshit.

236
00:12:51,891 --> 00:12:53,191
You think she's gonna
let her baby

237
00:12:53,192 --> 00:12:55,394
rot in jail for a cause?

238
00:12:58,030 --> 00:12:59,930
I don't know what to do.

239
00:13:01,199 --> 00:13:03,367
What would you do?

240
00:13:03,368 --> 00:13:05,536
If it was my kid,
or if it was me?

241
00:13:05,537 --> 00:13:07,304
You were in the service, right?

242
00:13:07,305 --> 00:13:08,506
I was.

243
00:13:08,507 --> 00:13:10,408
You see action?

244
00:13:15,346 --> 00:13:17,414
It was very different.

245
00:13:17,415 --> 00:13:20,316
I wanted to go.

246
00:13:20,317 --> 00:13:22,819
And then when
I got there, well...

247
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:24,921
That's the trick.

248
00:13:24,922 --> 00:13:27,457
Kids 18, 19 years old, they have
no sense of their own mortality.

249
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:29,358
Or anyone else's.

250
00:13:29,359 --> 00:13:31,093
That's why they make
good soldiers.

251
00:13:31,094 --> 00:13:33,695
Well, the Army
paid for med school.

252
00:13:33,696 --> 00:13:37,032
I served in a hospital
in Pusan.

253
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:39,367
We were very lucky.

