00:26:51,433 --> 00:26:53,133
You're not interested?

506
00:26:53,134 --> 00:26:54,868
No.

507
00:26:54,869 --> 00:26:56,737
Then why are you using
your sexy voice?

508
00:26:58,205 --> 00:27:00,107
Tuesday morning's great.

509
00:27:00,108 --> 00:27:01,541
For what?

510
00:27:01,542 --> 00:27:03,977
Oh.

511
00:27:03,978 --> 00:27:05,345
Why didn't you say so?

512
00:27:05,346 --> 00:27:08,048
You can bring her.

513
00:27:08,049 --> 00:27:10,349
It'll be dead by morning.

514
00:27:21,152 --> 00:27:23,353
Eleanor Roosevelt.

515
00:27:23,354 --> 00:27:26,289
I can't remember anything
'cause I didn't sleep.

516
00:27:26,290 --> 00:27:28,124
Your floor smells like pee.

517
00:27:28,125 --> 00:27:30,760
- No, it doesn't.
- Do I smell like pee?

518
00:27:30,761 --> 00:27:32,294
You smell like Prell.

519
00:27:32,295 --> 00:27:33,863
Sally, you're not ready?

520
00:27:33,864 --> 00:27:35,564
I let the guest shower first.

521
00:27:35,565 --> 00:27:37,533
Well, I have to go to work.

522
00:27:37,534 --> 00:27:39,669
But first I have to put you
two in a cab, so shake a leg.

523
00:27:39,670 --> 00:27:41,537
Oh, take out the trash.

524
00:27:41,538 --> 00:27:43,438
I have to get ready.

525
00:27:44,606 --> 00:27:46,507
I'll do it, Mrs. Draper.

526
00:27:46,508 --> 00:27:48,242
It's Megan.

527
00:27:48,243 --> 00:27:50,812
I would love to visit
the studio sometime.

528
00:27:50,813 --> 00:27:53,048
Well, hopefully
I'll still have a job.

529
00:27:53,049 --> 00:27:54,983
I have to make a phone call.

530
00:27:54,984 --> 00:27:57,585
- Your agent?
- Yes, actually.

531
00:28:09,197 --> 00:28:10,898
Could you get me some coffee?

532
00:28:16,003 --> 00:28:18,370
What the hell were you
up to last night?

533
00:28:18,371 --> 00:28:20,239
<i>Mr. Draper.</i>

534
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:23,142
I'm fine, Dawn.
You want some coffee?

535
00:28:23,143 --> 00:28:24,944
What the hell
were you thinking?

536
00:28:24,945 --> 00:28:28,114
You said you weren't going to be
involved in Chevy until 1970.

537
00:28:28,115 --> 00:28:30,016
So stay the hell out of it.

538
00:28:30,017 --> 00:28:31,817
Stop trying to poison
my relationship.

539
00:28:31,818 --> 00:28:34,052
Last time I checked,
it's <i>our</i> relationship.

540
00:28:34,053 --> 00:28:35,887
And not everything
is about you, Ted.

541
00:28:35,888 --> 00:28:37,756
Then be better at it.

542
00:28:37,757 --> 00:28:39,991
- What are you talking about?
- You know this.

543
00:28:39,992 --> 00:28:43,461
A client shouldn't have a single
negative feeling in your presence.

544
00:28:43,462 --> 00:28:45,731
Not the food, not the wine,

545
00:28:45,732 --> 00:28:47,765
and certainly not the war.

546
00:28:47,766 --> 00:28:48,933
I was just taking
their temperature.

547
00:28:48,934 --> 00:28:51,168
Why would you do that?

548
00:28:51,169 --> 00:28:52,703
It's Chevy, Don.

549
00:28:52,704 --> 00:28:55,672
- You'd do it for your kid.
- But it's not your kid.

550
00:28:55,673 --> 00:28:58,008
Oh, is it your kid?

551
00:28:58,009 --> 00:29:00,344
No, it's my friend's kid.

552
00:29:08,753 --> 00:29:10,386
Well, I bet you don't have
a lot of friends, Don,

553
00:29:10,387 --> 00:29:12,288
so I'm going to assume
this is important.

554
00:29:12,289 --> 00:29:14,124
It is.

555
00:29:16,026 --> 00:29:19,095
I just--
I don't know what to do.

556
00:29:19,096 --> 00:29:21,096
Do you know how young 19 is?

557
00:29:21,097 --> 00:29:22,998
Did you ever think
about talking to me

558
00:29:22,999 --> 00:29:24,432
instead of our most
important client?

559
00:29:24,433 --> 00:29:26,101
I don't know.
It's GM.

560
00:29:26,102 --> 00:29:28,804
Who else has that kind
of clout in Washington?

561
00:29:28,805 --> 00:29:30,505
Does he wear glasses?

562
00:29:30,506 --> 00:29:32,841
I don't think so, but he could.

563
00:29:35,211 --> 00:29:37,578
The guy who taught me to fly

564
00:29:37,579 --> 00:29:40,581
is a brigadier general
in the Air National Guard.

565
00:29:40,582 --> 00:29:42,483
They're always looking
for exceptional young men

566
00:29:42,484 --> 00:29:44,819
to become pilots.

567
00:29:46,488 --> 00:29:48,555
And you'd be willing
to call him?

568
00:29:48,556 --> 00:29:50,758
I'd consider it.

569
00:29:50,759 --> 00:29:53,660
But first, you're going
to have to stop the war.

570
00:29:53,661 --> 00:29:55,428
I can't stop the war, Ted.

571
00:29:55,429 --> 00:29:56,763
Don't be an asshole, Don.

572
00:29:56,764 --> 00:29:58,464
The war you're waging on me.

573
00:29:58,465 --> 00:30:00,133
You have to lower your weapons.

574
00:30:00,134 --> 00:30:01,902
What are you talking about?

575
00:30:01,903 --> 00:30:04,805
I'm talking about how we
are going to get Ocean Spray.

576
00:30:04,806 --> 00:30:07,640
So you need to stop
chasing Sunkist.

577
00:30:07,641 --> 00:30:10,242
You're not going to compete
with me like that anymore.

578
00:30:10,243 --> 00:30:12,477
We're on the same damn side.

579
00:30:12,478 --> 00:30:16,248
- That's it?
- Don't act like it's nothing.

580
00:30:16,249 --> 00:30:18,483
It seems to be
impossible so far.

581
00:30:21,054 --> 00:30:23,755
You'd really do that?

582
00:30:33,065 --> 00:30:34,432
Thank you.

583
00:30:34,433 --> 00:30:36,000
This is not
a handshake of gratitude.

584
00:30:36,001 --> 00:30:38,569
- This is a binding contract.
- Of course.

585
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:41,771
- Whatever you want.
- That's what I want.

586
00:30:44,342 --> 00:30:47,044
Hold on.
What's the next step?

587
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:49,279
Tell the kid to write a letter

588
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:51,681
about his childhood
dream of being a pilot.

589
00:30:51,682 --> 00:30:54,084
And it better be convincing.
You should write it.

590
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:56,785
And tell him to get a haircut.

591
00:30:56,786 --> 00:31:00,857
Be straight, Ted.
What are the chances?

592
00:31:00,858 --> 00:31:02,825
I'm going to call right now.

593
00:31:02,826 --> 00:31:04,526
Thank you.

594
00:31:10,033 --> 00:31:12,334
Can you get Dr. Rosen
on the phone?

595
00:31:19,909 --> 00:31:23,378
- Rosen residence.
- It's me. It's Don.

596
00:31:23,379 --> 00:31:24,913
What do you want?

597
00:31:24,914 --> 00:31:26,748
I'm trying to reach Arnold.

598
00:31:26,749 --> 00:31:29,449
<i>The office said</i>
<i>he was home sick.</i>

599
00:31:29,450 --> 00:31:31,285
It's about Mitchell.

600
00:31:31,286 --> 00:31:33,053
What? Tell me.

601
00:31:33,054 --> 00:31:35,923
I know someone who knows someone
in the Air National Guard.

602
00:31:35,924 --> 00:31:38,359
He's getting him a spot.

603
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,160
You told someone?

604
00:31:40,161 --> 00:31:41,661
It's my partner.

605
00:31:41,662 --> 00:31:43,864
He's doing me a favor.

606
00:31:48,735 --> 00:31:51,670
Did you fix it?

607
00:31:51,671 --> 00:31:53,172
He just wants Mitchell
to cut his hair

608
00:31:53,173 --> 00:31:55,808
and sign a letter.

609
00:31:55,809 --> 00:31:58,311
And the two of you need to
make sure he follows through.

610
00:31:58,312 --> 00:32:00,178
Oh, he'll follow through.

611
00:32:01,747 --> 00:32:03,448
I bet.

612
00:32:08,121 --> 00:32:10,255
My God, is it possible?

613
00:32:10,256 --> 00:32:12,991
I think so,
but we have to act fast.

614
00:32:12,992 --> 00:32:16,161
They went upstate to the VA
to call on an army buddy.

615
00:32:16,162 --> 00:32:18,596
I'll send them up tonight.

616
00:32:18,597 --> 00:32:20,698
Sylvia, sweetheart,
it's gonna be okay.

617
00:32:29,241 --> 00:32:32,243
Are you there?

618
00:32:32,244 --> 00:32:34,110
Yes.

619
00:32:34,111 --> 00:32:36,647
Please, stop crying.

620
00:32:36,648 --> 00:32:38,982
I feel better,

621
00:32:38,983 --> 00:32:41,284
but I'll feel better
when I know it's done.

622
00:32:45,890 --> 00:32:47,991
Don...

623
00:32:47,992 --> 00:32:50,092
Yes?

624
00:32:51,595 --> 00:32:53,629
I can't believe you
would do this for me.

625
00:32:53,630 --> 00:32:56,466
You know I have children, too.

626
00:32:56,467 --> 00:32:59,435
I know that's not
why you're doing it.

627
00:33:01,872 --> 00:33:04,739
And I hope--

628
00:33:04,740 --> 00:33:07,943
well, I hope you know that I
was just frustrated with you.

629
00:33:10,813 --> 00:33:12,981
I do now.

630
00:33:15,117 --> 00:33:18,453
I didn't want you
to fall in love.

631
00:33:18,454 --> 00:33:20,855
You didn't feel anything?

632
00:33:27,095 --> 00:33:29,329
No, I just...

633
00:33:31,867 --> 00:33:34,267
I don't want
to go through this again.

634
00:33:37,237 --> 00:33:39,639
You were good to me.

635
00:33:41,475 --> 00:33:44,176
Better than I was to you.

636
00:33:51,218 --> 00:33:53,584
- Are we going to lunch, because--
- Get in here and close the door.

637
00:33:56,255 --> 00:33:58,123
You have given me
a terrible problem

638
00:33:58,124 --> 00:33:59,390
and now you're going to fix it.

639
00:33:59,391 --> 00:34:01,893
Is this about Sunkist?
Because I did some digging--

640
00:34:01,894 --> 00:34:05,230
I told you we needed a nurse
and you sent us a rapist.

641
00:34:05,231 --> 00:34:06,564
Manolo?

642
00:34:06,565 --> 00:34:08,066
In fact, I never
told you anything.

643
00:34:08,067 --> 00:34:09,666
You were just
"doing some digging."

644
00:34:09,667 --> 00:34:12,069
Calm down.
Sit down.

645
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:17,241
Bob...

646
00:34:17,242 --> 00:34:19,910
she has the mind of a child.

647
00:34:19,911 --> 00:34:21,778
That man took advantage of her.

648
00:34:21,779 --> 00:34:25,081
I assume she told
you this story.

649
00:34:25,082 --> 00:34:27,150
Don't you have
your answer right there?

650
00:34:27,151 --> 00:34:28,885
She says they're in love

651
00:34:28,886 --> 00:34:31,321
and it's the first time in months
she's seemed sure of anything.

652
00:34:31,322 --> 00:34:35,624
I don't think that Manolo's
interests turn that way.

653
00:34:35,625 --> 00:34:38,061
Great, so he's a degenerate.

654
00:34:38,062 --> 00:34:40,196
That means he's capable
of anything.

655
00:34:44,234 --> 00:34:47,169
What exactly did she say?

656
00:34:47,170 --> 00:34:49,905
Please, I'm just
trying to forget it.

657
00:34:49,906 --> 00:34:52,007
Drink that.

658
00:34:58,347 --> 00:35:02,950
- Feel better now?
- I do.

659
00:35:02,951 --> 00:35:04,518
Can I ask you something?

660
00:35:05,553 --> 00:35:07,454
Did she seem happy?

661
00:35:08,323 --> 00:35:10,624
Yes.

662
00:35:10,625 --> 00:35:12,459
She did.

663
00:35:18,966 --> 00:35:21,968
Is it really
so impossible to imagine?

664
00:35:21,969 --> 00:35:25,105
What?

665
00:35:25,106 --> 00:35:26,739
Couldn't it be that

666
00:35:26,740 --> 00:35:30,142
if someone took care of you,

667
00:35:30,143 --> 00:35:32,711
very good care of you...

668
00:35:34,414 --> 00:35:37,283
if this person would do
anything for you,

669
00:35:37,284 --> 00:35:41,020
if your well-being
was his only thought...

670
00:35:43,256 --> 00:35:45,456
is it impossible that you might

671
00:35:45,457 --> 00:35:48,092
begin to feel something
for him?

672
00:35:50,495 --> 00:35:53,664
When there's true love,

673
00:35:53,665 --> 00:35:56,234
it doesn't matter who it is.

674
00:36:12,817 --> 00:36:15,618
Tell him I'll give him
a month's pay.

675
00:36:15,619 --> 00:36:18,787
And tell him it's disgusting.

676
00:36:22,892 --> 00:36:25,061
Of course.

677
00:36:35,504 --> 00:36:37,839
The capital of the
Philippines is Manila.

678
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:40,808
Its president
is Ferdinand Marcos.

679
00:36:40,809 --> 00:36:43,044
Its national language
is Tagalog,

680
00:36:43,045 --> 00:36:45,646
but many of its
inhabitants speak Spanish

681
00:36:45,647 --> 00:36:47,715
due to its colonial past.

682
00:36:47,716 --> 00:36:50,684
And their national
product is...?

683
00:36:50,685 --> 00:36:53,954
I don't know.
Manila envelopes?

684
00:36:53,955 --> 00:36:57,357
- You don't know anything.
- So?

685
00:36:57,358 --> 00:36:59,593
How about this? All the boys are
going to think you're dumb.

686
00:36:59,594 --> 00:37:01,628
Don't tell me how to get boys.

687
00:37:01,629 --> 00:37:03,697
You went to second base twice.

688
00:37:03,698 --> 00:37:06,666
That's a lot more than you.

689
00:37:06,667 --> 00:37:08,869
So if I were you,
I'd be scared.

690
00:37:08,870 --> 00:37:11,471
- Of what?
- Of what you're going to do

691
00:37:11,472 --> 00:37:13,572
when Mitchell asks you
to go all the way.

692
00:37:13,573 --> 00:37:15,541
He doesn't even know I'm alive.

693
00:37:15,542 --> 00:37:18,677
Oh, I took care of that.

694
00:37:18,678 --> 00:37:20,412
What did you do?

695
00:37:20,413 --> 00:37:21,914
I introduced you.

696
00:37:21,915 --> 00:37:23,549
I introduced myself.

697
00:37:23,550 --> 00:37:27,119
No, I took the letter
and I signed your name.

698
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:30,087
- What?!
- And I slid it under the back door.

699
00:37:30,088 --> 00:37:32,690
Ow! That really hurts.

700
00:37:32,691 --> 00:37:34,592
How could you do that?
Now I can never go back.

701
00:37:34,593 --> 00:37:36,661
You know you're going
to thank me.

702
00:37:43,923 --> 00:37:45,122
Just because your shift is over

703
00:37:45,123 --> 00:37:47,058
doesn't mean you can get
undressed in the lobby.

704
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:54,087
- Incredible.
- What?

705
00:37:54,088 --> 00:37:56,957
He should greet you.
How you doing today?

706
00:37:56,958 --> 00:38:00,994
I'm-- I got--
I left something.

707
00:38:00,995 --> 00:38:02,730
And I don't have my key.

708
00:38:02,731 --> 00:38:04,865
You mean you lost it already?

709
00:38:04,866 --> 00:38:07,066
Can I have the keys, please?

710
00:38:09,903 --> 00:38:12,304
Yeah. Okay.

711
00:38:13,907 --> 00:38:15,675
<i>Go fast.</i>

712
00:38:19,513 --> 00:38:20,980
Oh, what have we got here?

713
00:38:20,981 --> 00:38:22,848
<i>Couple of high fashion models?</i>

714
00:38:55,413 --> 00:38:57,447
Oh, God.

715
00:39:05,123 --> 00:39:07,624
- Sally.
- Oh, God.

716
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:10,760
Oh, dear God.

717
00:39:12,830 --> 00:39:15,264
Dear God, what have we done?

718
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,707
Sally!

719
00:39:28,912 --> 00:39:31,413
Sally!

720
00:39:31,414 --> 00:39:33,381
Sally!

721
00:40:01,041 --> 00:40:02,442
Did Sally just come
through here?

722
00:40:02,443 --> 00:40:04,210
Mr. Draper, I didn't
know you was home.

723
00:40:04,211 --> 00:40:05,879
She hopped in a cab just now.
I'll go get her.

724
00:40:08,583 --> 00:40:10,951
You okay?

725
00:40:10,952 --> 00:40:12,519
Yes.

726
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:14,554
Did something happen?

727
00:40:14,555 --> 00:40:17,490
I know she lost her keys. I gave
her the keys. It's my fault.

728
00:40:31,904 --> 00:40:33,972
Mr. Draper?

729
00:42:16,469 --> 00:42:18,536
<i>Hello?</i>

730
00:42:31,683 --> 00:42:33,985
Oh, I'm glad you're home.

731
00:42:36,688 --> 00:42:39,520
Let me get you a plate.

732
00:42:39,521 --> 00:42:41,355
Oh, wow.

733
00:42:41,356 --> 00:42:43,290
I had a client...

734
00:42:43,291 --> 00:42:45,292
meeting-- lunch.

735
00:42:45,293 --> 00:42:47,661
- Sit down.
- I'm--

736
00:42:47,662 --> 00:42:49,530
I'm gonna lay down.

737
00:42:49,531 --> 00:42:51,799
You need to get some food in you.
Sit down.

738
00:42:53,802 --> 00:42:56,268
Do you want me
to cut you a piece?

739
00:42:58,806 --> 00:43:01,007
No.

740
00:43:01,008 --> 00:43:02,774
I got it.

741
00:43:05,412 --> 00:43:07,513
<i>Hello.</i>

742
00:43:07,514 --> 00:43:09,648
I'm sorry to bother you.

743
00:43:09,649 --> 00:43:11,984
Don, Arnold and
Mitchell <i>are here.</i>

744
00:43:13,586 --> 00:43:15,488
- I don't feel well.
- Stop.

745
00:43:19,258 --> 00:43:20,791
Hello, Mitchell.

746
00:43:20,792 --> 00:43:22,660
I'm sorry
to interrupt your dinner,

747
00:43:22,661 --> 00:43:24,962
but we just got back and Mitchell
has something he wants to say.

748
00:43:28,634 --> 00:43:30,768
Mr. Draper...

749
00:43:33,172 --> 00:43:35,806
thank you very much.

750
00:43:36,942 --> 00:43:38,709
We'll see if it works.

751
00:43:38,710 --> 00:43:41,211
- What?
- He didn't tell you?

752
00:43:42,614 --> 00:43:44,749
Don talked to somebody for us.

753
00:43:44,750 --> 00:43:46,083
Really?

754
00:43:46,084 --> 00:43:48,653
Sylvia sends her gratitude.
She is overwhelmed.

755
00:43:50,721 --> 00:43:53,356
Do you want something to eat?
We should celebrate.

756
00:43:53,357 --> 00:43:55,391
One step at a time.

757
00:43:55,392 --> 00:43:58,595
Anyway, Don,

758
00:43:58,596 --> 00:44:00,430
I owe you.

759
00:44:03,333 --> 00:44:06,102
Let's go.

760
00:44:06,103 --> 00:44:07,703
No, you eat. I got it.

761
00:44:11,507 --> 00:44:13,709
You are the sweetest man.

762
00:44:15,511 --> 00:44:17,446
You make me sick!

763
00:44:18,648 --> 00:44:20,916
Sally, come back here!

764
00:44:20,917 --> 00:44:23,017
What happened?

765
00:44:23,018 --> 00:44:24,786
I don't know.

766
00:44:24,787 --> 00:44:25,987
